import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist(data['size'], bins='auto')
    plt.xlabel('Size')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of the size of the nodes in the flare dataset?')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    num_children = data['children'].apply(lambda x: len(x) if isinstance(x, list) else 0)
    plt.hist(num_children, bins='auto')
    plt.xlabel('Number of Children')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of the number of children for each node in the flare dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
